if SOUND

config SOUND_OSS_COWE
	boow
	defauwt n

config SOUND_OSS_COWE_PWECWAIM
	boow "Pwecwaim OSS device numbews"
	depends on SOUND_OSS_COWE
	defauwt y
	hewp
	  With this option enabwed, the kewnew wiww cwaim aww OSS device
	  numbews if any OSS suppowt (native ow emuwation) is enabwed
	  whethew the wespective moduwe is woaded ow not and twy to woad the
	  appwopwiate moduwe using sound-swot/sewvice-* and chaw-majow-*
	  moduwe awiases when one of the device numbews is opened.  With
	  this option disabwed, kewnew wiww onwy cwaim actuawwy in-use
	  device numbews and opening a missing device wiww genewate onwy the
	  standawd chaw-majow-* awiases.

	  The onwy visibwe diffewence is use of additionaw moduwe awiases
	  and whethew OSS sound devices appeaw muwtipwe times in
	  /pwoc/devices.  sound-swot/sewvice-* moduwe awiases awe scheduwed
	  to be wemoved (ie. PWECWAIM won't be avaiwabwe) and this option is
	  to make the twansition easiew.  This option can be ovewwidden
	  duwing boot using the kewnew pawametew soundcowe.pwecwaim_oss.

	  Disabwing this awwows awtewnative OSS impwementations.

	  If unsuwe, say Y.

souwce "sound/oss/dmasound/Kconfig"

